The Chronicle Bongani Ndlovu, Chronicle Reporter THE country recorded 839 new Covid-19 positive cases and 15 deaths in the last 24 hours. There are 838 local cases and one is a returnee from Zambia. A total of 3 010 PCR tests were conducted. New recoveries were 255. The national recovery rate stands at 60,7 percent and active cases went up to 7 577. “As of 9 January, 2020, Zimbabwe has now recorded 20 499 cases, 12 439 recoveries and 483 deaths,” reads statistics from the Ministry of Health and Child Care.